comment_regular_data.body:
Hi ! I think the PR is functional now. The output of `pwsh` are quite noisy, that is why tests are weird, searching in the string rather than considering it entirely. I can add a comment for that in the tests.

@justinmk I would be more than happy to address any comments/concerns/refactors, feel free to let me know.

As a synthesis of the effect, this pull request is aiming at making `&shell` the default filtering program for `:range!` command. However, there was an original feature with the `!{motion}` command that remembered the previously given filtering program. I tried to preserve the latter behavior while setting the default filtering program __on startup__ as the `&shell`
